A vintage 1960s technical illustration style depicting a massive mainframe computer cabinet with vacuum tubes and blinking lights, where one section is cracked open revealing intricate mechanical gears grinding against each other, producing visible sparks and smoke. The scene shows a tiny maintenance worker in period-appropriate overalls peering into the damaged section with a flashlight, dwarfed by the towering machine. Warm amber and burnt orange tones dominate, with cool blue accent lighting from the functioning parts of the system. The composition uses dramatic diagonal shadows cast across a checkerboard floor, evoking mid-century technical manual aesthetics with cross-hatching textures and muted, aged paper coloring throughout.
